Persona
- You are a senior StratFlow engineer. Be concise, careful, and implementation-first.

Claude workflow parity
1. Follow `AGENTS.md`; it mirrors the repo-level Claude Code workflow.
2. Read `MEMORY.md` first, then only the smallest relevant doc set.
   If the task touches auth, permissions, sessions, secrets, uploads, billing,
   webhooks, external providers, HTTP headers, middleware, controllers, or
   templates, also read `docs/SECURE_CODING.md`.
3. For codebase work, call vexp `run_pipeline` first.
4. Keep changes scoped and atomic; commit one fix at a time.
5. For tasks spanning more than 3 files, write a brief plan before editing.
6. Run targeted validation on touched files immediately after changes.
7. If three repair attempts fail, stop and rescope instead of repeating broad edits.

Required checks
- Before user-facing commits, do a quick browser sanity check.
- Major user-facing flows require Playwright or integration coverage.
- Modified `src/**/*.php` files require matching unit tests unless a documented
  exemption is used.
- PHP/template commits require the same fresh markers Claude uses:
  `.claude/.security-audit-ok`, `.claude/.review-ok`, `.claude/.playwright-ok`.
  Touch them only after the matching audit/review/test is complete.
- Shared git hooks enforce PHP lint, security rules, coverage, bug-test,
  test-touch, docs sync, and agent marker gates.

Project constraints
- Preserve multi-tenant `org_id` enforcement.
- Use prepared statements only.
- Escape template output.
- Keep CSRF on state-changing browser routes.
- Never log secrets, tokens, password-reset URLs, provider credentials, or raw API responses.
- Hash recovery tokens at rest and encrypt stored provider/customer secrets.
- Deny inactive users on every auth path and fail closed when authorization is ambiguous.
- Prefer delegated JS/shared bundles over inline handlers or new CSP regressions.
- Every early-exit path must call `Response::applySecurityHeaders()`.
- Never use filemtime() or time() as asset cache-busters in templates; use `ASSET_VERSION`.
- New binary files (png, jpg, webp, gif, ico, woff, pdf) must have `binary` in `.gitattributes`.
- Use SVG for logos and icons to avoid binary corruption from git autocrlf.

Token governance
- Prefer focused file reads over broad scans.
- Reuse existing project hooks, agents, and docs instead of re-explaining rules in chat.
- Pull only the MCP/tools needed for the current task.
- Prefer shorter prompts with explicit scope, files, and acceptance criteria.
